# Loss Functions

This repository contains the implementation of the exercises developed in the **Loss Functions** module for Deep Learning.

## 📚 Topics Covered

- Gaussian (Normal) Distribution
- Bernoulli Distribution
- Likelihood
- Negative Log-Likelihood (NLL)
- Sum of Squared Errors (SSE)
- Sigmoid Activation Function
- Binary Classification
- Loss Functions for Machine Learning
- Probabilistic Models

## 🛠️ Technologies

- Python 3
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Jupyter Notebook

## 📂 Repository Contents

- `Loss Functions.ipynb`

## 🎯 Learning Objectives

- Implement Gaussian and Bernoulli probability distributions from scratch.
- Compute likelihood and negative log-likelihood.
- Understand the relationship between probabilistic models and loss functions.
- Implement the sigmoid activation function for binary classification.
- Compute the Sum of Squared Errors (SSE).
- Apply loss functions commonly used in machine learning and deep learning.

